\pard\li2793\sb198\sl253\slmult0\tx5913\cf1\expndtw-5\b\f0\fs22 52 \expndtw0\b0\tab\b\i A Guide to \i0 Church Planting\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\li2798\ri104\sb142\sl275\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 who have come from other churches or evangelical groups should be examined, too, since to fail to do so may introduce a weak or divisive element into the new church.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi235\li2827\ri90\sb3\sl271\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 It would be wise for the worker to form an examining committee of the most mature Christians to consult with them about the candidates for membership. In this way, the members begin to share in the responsibility in the operation of the church from its inception.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi225\li2870\ri51\sb4\sl270\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 Once there is a list of members, the next step is to confirm the worker who is to serve as pastor by obtaining the ap-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 proval of the body of believers. In the beginning this might seem to be an almost unnecessary procedure, since the new congregation will normally accept the worker they know, or \expndtw3 the worker who is suggested to them without question. How-\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 ever, we are teaching the new congregation the responsibil-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 ities which they must bear in the future, and it is preferable to introduce correct practices right from the beginning rather than to effect changes later on.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi225\li2913\ri18\sl272\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 If the new church is formed as a result of the growth of \super\fs33 an \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 outstation of a mother church, the pastor of the mother \super\fs33 church, \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw2\b\f0 together with the official board will counsel the worker in t\expndtw0\super\fs33 he \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 development of the new church. The candidates for baptis\super\fs33 m \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\dn4\f0 will be examined by the board of the mother church in the \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\b\f0 usual way, until the new group is formed into an autono\expndtw0\super\fs33 mous \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 church. If a national organization exists, the m\super\fs33 atter of the \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 time in which the group can achieve autonomy wil\super\fs33 l be de-\cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 cided in consultation among \super\fs33 the local worker,\nosupersub\fs22  the pas\super\fs33 tor of \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 the mother church, and th\super\fs33 e officers of the national organiza-\cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 tion.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi235\li2913\ri3\sl271\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 After choosing its pastor, the \super\fs33 church is now ready to elect \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 its official board. Usually \super\fs33 from three to seven deacons are \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw3\b\f0 chosen. For a small chu\expndtw0\super\fs33 rch, the smaller number is preferable, \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 particularly as it is unl\super\fs33 ikely that there will be sufficient ma-\cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\par

