\pard\li53\sb99\sl253\slmult0\tx5867\cf1\b\i\f0\fs22 Establishing the \i0 Church \b0\tab\expndtw-5\b 53\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi14\li39\ri1359\sb141\sl271\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 tore men to fill the posts. If all the members of the congrega-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 tion are new converts, it would be better to appoint an advisory committee and have the members ratified by \i the \i0 congregation, rather than to choose deacons at the start. This advisory committee could work with the pastor for a year and become acquainted with the organization and \i manage-\cf0\b0\i0\f1\line\cf1\b\i\f0 ment \i0 of church business.  Perhaps by the second year it would be possible to elect deacons if there are those who are \expndtw1 qualified to fill these posts.\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi230\li29\ri1384\sb3\sl266\slmult0\qj\tx2713\cf1\expndtw2\b\f0 It is important to hold \expndtw0\b0\tab\expndtw2\b closely as possible to the standards \expndtw0 for deacons as outlined in the Scriptures. Acts 6:1-6 and 1 \expndtw2 Timothy 3:7-13 will serve as a guide.\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi244\li15\ri1393\sb16\sl268\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 It should be understood that the deacons are chosen pri-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw3\b\f0 marily to relieve the pastor of certain material responsibilities \expndtw0 related to the congregation. The New Testament church had elders who served in the spiritual area of church government and ministry. In modern practice, the pastor is usually the only one who is recognized as an elder, unless he has an as-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 sistant. In view of this, deacons are often pressed into spir-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 itual responsibilities and must serve as a board of administra-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 tion in spiritual as well as material things. The matter of church discipline, for example, is usually handled by the pastor and the board of deacons.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi230\li10\ri1394\sb44\sl275\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 The new church should probably hold a business meeting \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 once a year to confirm the pastor, or call a new one, and to \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 elect the official board. As the church becomes more estab-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 lished and the deacons have more experience, they \fs26 may be \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 elected for three-year terms. Some churches have found it \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 helpful to terminate the positions on different years. For \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 example, a three-deacon board the first time would be elected \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw3\b\f0 in this way: One deacon for a three-year term, another deacon \cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 for \i a \i0 two-year term, and a third deacon for a one-year term.\cf0\b0\f1\par

