\pard\li10\ri898\sb5\sl300\slmult0\qj\cf1\expndtw2\b\f0 IN THE Fran c:HAPTEa, it was pointed out that the church has \cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\up4\f0\fs24 a three-fold reason for being: to minister to God; to minister \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 to the believers; and to minister to the world in evangelism.\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li1469\sb210\sl276\slmult1\cf1\expndtw-8\b\dn4\f0\fs24 THE CHURCH'S NILVISTRY TO GOD\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi240\li10\ri894\sb97\sl301\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\up0\f0\fs24 Acts 13 presents a functioning church in Antioch which \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 became a missionary base for the spreading of the gospel to \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 the Gentiles. As they ministered to the Lord, the Holy Spirit \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 told them to set aside Barnabas and Saul for their missionary \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 ministry (v. 2). What does the term "ministered to the Lord," \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 really mean?  The underlying concept is that of worship. \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 Jesus said, "The true worshipers shall worship the Father in \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 spirit and in truth: for the Father seeketh such to worship \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 Him" ( Jn 4:23). In Romans \fs22 12:1, \fs24 we are told that our reason-\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 able service (or spiritual worship) consists not of offering \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 sacrifices of animals which have been slain, but in the pre-\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 senting of our bodies as a living sacrifice to God. In other \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 words, spiritual worship does not consist simply in the ob-\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 servance of religious rituals, but in the presentation of our \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 life in service to God. Our consecration to God is an accept-\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs24 able spiritual worship. Worship also includes thanksgiving \cf0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw1\b\f0\fs24 and praise to God \fs26 and \fs24 adoration in \fs26 which we recognize God's\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

