\pard\li10\sb97\sl176\slmult0\tx5756\cf1\b\i\f0\fs22 The Church in Action \b0\i0\tab\expndtw-7\b 57\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\fs12\par

\pard\li2903\ri57\sb101\sl272\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0\fs22 majesty and worth ( Heb 13:15-16 ). We are told that giving our gifts to God constitutes a form of spiritual sacrifice that pleases God ( Phil 4:18). Also, doing good and serving hu-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 manity is a service or an act of worship to God.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi249\li2913\ri86\sb3\sl276\slmult1\qj\cf1\b\f0 It is necessary for us to realize that the function of the \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 church in worship is carried on not only when the congrega-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 tion is in the church building, but takes place every day as \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 Christians render service to God in prayer, in their offerings, \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 and in their service to humanity. Servants are exhorted to \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 serve their masters, not as menpleasers, but as servants of \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 God doing the will of God from the heart (Eph 6:6 ), so that \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 even humble household duties performed with the purpose \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 of pleasing God become an act of worship.  There is also \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 worship in a corporate sense when the church is assembled. \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 Evidently the Antioch church was engaged in this type of \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 spiritual service when the Holy Spirit spoke to the congre-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 gation ( Ac \fs20 13:1\fs22 -\fs20 2).\cf0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi302\li2870\ri110\sb42\sl281\slmult0\qj\tx2923\cf1\b\f0\fs20 It is \fs22 the function of the church leadership to stimulate an \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab\b atmosphere of true worship. Worship does not consist of \super\fs33 the \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 mechanical singing of hymns or the saying of p\super\fs33 rayers. These \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 activities may become an expression of wor\super\fs33 ship, but if they \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\i\f0 are \i0 performed mechanically and \super\fs33 routinely their performance \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 does not constitute true wors\super\fs33 hip. Jesus said that the worship \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 must be performed in spirit \super\fs33 and in truth. The heart must \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 be involved; there mus\super\fs33 t be sincerity and a true desire to draw \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 near to God. Moreo\super\fs33 ver, it takes more than human effort to \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 constitute true w\super\fs33 orship. The Holy Spirit must inspire and \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\dn4\f0 guide us in our worshi\super\fs33 p. Paul tells us that through Christ we \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 have access in o\super\fs33 ne Spirit unto the Father ( Eph \fs30 2:18). \fs33 Again, \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\i\f0 we are \i0 told tha\super\fs33 t we cannot pray as we ought "but the Spirit \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 itself maketh inte\super\fs33 rcession for us . . . according to the will of \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 God" (Ro 8:2\super\fs33 8-27). To attain true spiritual worship is the \cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0 highest func\super\fs33 tion of the church.\cf0\nosupersub\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li1209\sb193\sl253\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-8\b\f0\page THE CHURCH'S MINISTRY TO BELIEVERS\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi254\li91\ri1086\sb93\sl271\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\up0\f0 This ministry is both quantitative and qualitative. That is, the ministry of the church builds itself up in numbers and also in spiritual strength by maturing the spiritual life of the \expndtw1 individual members. Several different passages give emphasis \expndtw0 to this ministry. Ephesians \fs20 4:15\fs22 -\fs20 16 \fs22 points out that Christ is the Head of the body, and its members help each other mu-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw3\b\f0 tually by the operation of each member so that the individual \expndtw0 and the entire church are built up in love. The entire chapter \expndtw1 of 1 Corinthians 12 is devoted to the concept of the individual \expndtw0 Christian as a member of the body of Christ, and the contri-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 bution that each member can make to the whole.\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi249\li53\ri1143\sb11\sl268\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 The church is built up by love (1 Co 13) and by the exer-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 cise of spiritual gifts (1 Co \fs20 12:4\fs22 -\fs20 7). There follows \fs22 then a list \expndtw2 of spiritual gifts by which the church is built up and strength-\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 ened (1 Co 12:8-31; cf. Ro 12:4-10). \fs20 Some edify \fs22 the church by prophecy, exhortation, service, \fs20 and \fs22 teaching. The prin-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\b\f0 cipal ministries to the church (apostles, prophets, evangelists, \expndtw0 pastors and teachers) are for the purpose of preparing or "perfecting of the saints for the work of the ministry, for the edifying of the body of Christ" (Eph 4:11-13).\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi225\li33\ri1163\sb4\sl271\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 Prayer and intercession for the needs of our fellow be-\cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 lievers contribute to the strength of the different members of the church, and consequently the edification of the church itself (Eph 6:18-20; Ro 8:26-27).\cf0\b0\f1\par

\pard\fi235\li10\ri1178\sb11\sl273\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0 The service to the fellow members of the body of Christ is \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 enjoined as a way of edifying the body of Christ. "Do good \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 to all men, especially those of the household of faith" (Gal \cf0\b0\f1\line\cf1\b\f0 6:10).\cf0\b0\f1\par

