\pard\li10\sb94\sl192\slmult0\tx6337\cf1\i\f0 The Church \i0 in \i\fs22 Action \i0\fs24\tab\expndtw2\dn4 59\cf0\expndtw0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\up0\fs12\par

\pard\li2433\ri51\sb98\sl283\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 preach the gospel to every creature and to all nations \expndtw-7 ( Lk \expndtw0 24:47; Mt 28:16-20; Mk 16:15).\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi268\li2443\ri65\sb20\sl307\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 The coming of the Holy Spirit was to grant power to be-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 lievers to become witnesses to all nations (Ac 1:8).\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi264\li2448\ri2\sl300\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 A valid example and pattern is given by the early Chris-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 tians who "went everywhere preaching the Word" (Ac 8:4). \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 The testimony of the apostle Paul was that he "taught pub-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 l i cly, and from house to house, testifying both to the Jews \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 toward our Lord Jesus Christ (Ac 20:20-21).\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi268\li2443\ri41\sb1\sl304\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 As the closing days of this age approach God has com-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 manded the church to finish the task of total world evan-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 gelism. With the immense increase of population throughout the world, it is required that we use every legitimate means for spreading the gospel.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi297\li2400\ri26\sb4\sl305\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 The first and foremost means of spreading the gospel has always been, and will always be, the personal witness of Christians in their contacts with the unconverted. This effort can be backed up by the distribution of gospel literature, evangelism by radio, campaigns for mass evangelism, o\super\fs36 pen-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 air \i0 evangelism in the streets and parks, and evangelistic \super\fs36 cen-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 ters in ghettos and suburbs of the \super\fs36 cities.\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi297\li2361\ri17\sl307\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 Each congregation should \super\fs36 consider that the unevangelized1 \nosupersub\fs24 people in the area are its p\super\fs36 articular responsibility. Each \fs33 con-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 gregation is responsib\super\fs36 le to take the gospel message to the \nosupersub\fs24 territory continge\super\fs36 nt to its base, at least halfway to the next; \nosupersub\fs24 congregation.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi302\li2323\ri46\sl305\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 One of the first steps \super\fs36 should be a survey of the area in order! \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 to find the open d\super\fs36 oors for witness. These may be simply the \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 opportunity to p\super\fs36 reach in a home of a believer, or to hold a \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\dn4\f0\fs24 gospel service \super\fs36 in the open air in a nearby village. The \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 church leader\super\fs36 s then \i assign \i0 faithful lay workers to witness \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 weekly in eac\super\fs36 h place. \b A \b0 branch Sunday school should be\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi67\li134\ri605\sb190\sl299\slmult0\qj\tx232\tx222\tx217\cf1\up0\f0\fs24\page established, with teachers from the mother church helping in \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab this important outreach of their local church. Evening serv-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab ices should be initiated. As converts are won, the process of \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab teaching must be commenced to prepare the new group for \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 baptism.  Eventually the outstation can be organized as a \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 church, so that again the process of outreach and church \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 planting is repeated. This system of church extension is ef-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 fective in cities as well as in rural area. Like a strawberry \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 plant sends out its runners and produces new plants until the \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 area is filled, so the establishing of new churches by means of \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 lay preachers and outstations is a nonspectacular, but ef-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\dn4\f0\fs24 fective way to plant churches at the grass roots level.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi268\li96\ri715\sb16\sl291\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0\fs24 We have seen this method used in a city with such success \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 that a city with a beginning of \dn4 12 new churches, within 10 \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 years had multiplied until there were 40. This same method \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 in a rural area, coupled with a training program for workers, \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 has produced 100 churches within a radius of 30 miles of the \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 central city.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi297\li33\ri764\sb24\sl299\slmult0\qj\tx116\tx116\tx112\cf1\up0\f0\fs24 Emphasis must be continually placed on the participation \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab of the total body of believers in evangelism. Great spiritual \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab awakenings are always characterized by the zealous witness-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab ing and fervent prayer participation by the body of Christian \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 believers. As a revival loses its original impetus, the tendency \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 is to place more responsibility in the hands of a few leaders. \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 The activities tend to move out of the homes, the streets, and \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 the open air, and into the church building. The pastor as-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 sumes more and more the responsibility for evangelism until \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 the congregation's activity is mostly that of spectators. Thus \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 the evangelistic activity of the church tends to stagnate.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi268\li10\ri821\sb6\sl297\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs24 In order to keep the church growing and expanding, every \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 effort must be made to keep the congregation involved at the \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 very center of evangelistic outreach. This means that con-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24 stant emphasis must be placed on the day by day participa-\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\fs12\par
\par
\par

\pard\li2625\sl299\slmult0\fs24\par

