\pard\fi748\li1871\ri1497\sb159\sl254\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 The biblical, participatory, and spiritual aspects of church \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 administration find their clearest practical application in the \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 selection of the first missionaries. It seems clear in Acts 13 that \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the process of selecting and sending those missionaries depended \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 solely upon the sovereignty of the Holy Spirit through prayer. \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 The Holy Spirit selected the missionaries, and the Holy Spirit sent \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 them to a particular place. The local church served as an interme-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 diary agency, a physical representation of the hand of God in His \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 world.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li3595\sl253\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\li3595\sb205\sl253\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-8\f0\fs22 THE PURPOSE OF THE CHURCH\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi782\li1800\ri1540\sb156\sl264\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Without a clear-cut set of objectives, any organization suffers. The church has been less than outstanding in its clarifica-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 tion of mission in the late twentieth century. Not all church lead-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ers have been silent, however, and at least one leading educator has specified in print an attempt to answer the question, "What is the church for?"\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li1699\sl236\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\fi48\li2467\ri1554\sb32\sl236\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs22 The answer is no mystery. Scripture makes it plain that the \expndtw1 church is to be a worshipping body, committed to "show forth \expndtw0 the \fs20 praises \fs22 of him who has called (it) out of darkness into his marvelous light"; that it is to proclaim the saving gospel of Jesus Christ to all the world; and that it is to obey all the teach-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw-1\dn4\f0 ings of Jesus Christ, its great head and Lord.2\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi72\li1636\ri1578\sb254\sl282\slmult0\qj\tx1699\tx1684\cf1\f0 For thirty years Dr. Frank E. Gaeb\super\fs33 elein gave careful thought to \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs24\tab the issues \fs22 of Christian ed\super\fs33 ucation and philosophy. Unfortunately, \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\tab however, no one individu\super\fs33 al can speak for all local churches. Each \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 body of believers m\super\fs33 ust reassess the purpose of its own existence \nosupersub\fs24 and clarify \fs22 its relat\super\fs33 ionship to the universal church. The New Tes-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 tament seems to \super\fs33 set \fs36 forth four basic objectives for the church, \expndtw1\nosupersub\fs24 though church leade\expndtw0\super\fs36 rs may verbalize them differently.\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

