\pard\li1617\sb135\sl276\slmult1\cf1\expndtw-2\i\f0 The Church Develops a Strategy for Evangelism\cf0\expndtw0\i0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi748\li1588\ri1521\sb147\sl263\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Biblically, evangelism is the clear proclamation- of the gospel of Jesus Christ, leaving the results entirely up to the sover-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 eignty of the Holy Spirit. Some churches have viewed evangelism as the \i\fs24 only \i0\fs22 task of the church and have subordinated all other purposes to it. Unfortunately, such churches fill their rolls with baby Christians who, instead of growing week by week on the milk, bread, and meat of the Word, receive only a constant bar-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 rage of the elementary principles of the gospel.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi816\li1507\ri1530\sb5\sl270\slmult0\qj\tx1574\tx1564\tx1564\tx1560\cf1\dn4\f0 Such excesses, however, should not cloud the fact that \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab evangelism is a legitimate task of the church. Surely some have a \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab special gift of evangelism, but their ministry does not excuse the \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab responsibility of every Christian to communicate the gospel. Paul \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 speaks for the church in Ephesians 3:8 when he says of himself, \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab "This grace was given me: to preach to the Gentiles the unsearch-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\fs24 able riches \fs22 of Christ." In Acts 8:4, when the apostles remained at \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 Jerusalem for some reason during a mass persecution, Luke \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 records that the church "went about preaching the word" \fs18 (NASB).\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi801\li1459\ri1549\sl279\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0 Some would prefer to describe this concept of the church's \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 purpose as "service," a more inclusive word. God's people render \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 varied kinds of service through the church, and not all of them \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 have to do directly with evangelism. Perhaps \super\fs33 we can say that the \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\dn4\f0 church both \i\fs24 has \i0\fs22 a mission \super\fs33 in the world and \i\fs36 is \i0\fs33 a mission in the \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 world.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li1440\sl320\slmult0\up0\fs24\par

