\pard\li2726\sb166\sl253\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-8\f0\fs22 UNDERSTANDING THE CHURCH\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi791\li911\ri1424\sb142\sl274\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 In recent years defining and describing a philosophy of \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ministry has created much confusion and no little controversy. \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 Yet as we study the New Testament, we seem to find at least a \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 minimal boundary of inclusion/exclusion to help us understand \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the local church. Writing from the context of congregational \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 polity, I would like to suggest that the local church is \i\fs24 a body of \cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 confessed believers joining together for worship, fellowship, \cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 instruction, and evangelism; led in its efforts by biblical officers \cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 (elders and deacons); and including, as part of its life and min-\cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 istry, observance of the ordinances, discipline, and mutual edifi-\cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 cation.\cf0\i0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi792\li868\ri1477\sl281\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Theologian Robert Culver enumerates six characteristics \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 of a local church: spiritual vitality, doctrinal instruction, fellow-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\dn4\f0 ship, observance of the Lord's Supper, prayer, and Chri\super\fs33 stian testi-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 mony) The popular apologist Francis Schaeffer \super\fs33 indicated eight \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 ingredients that must be a part of "the pol\super\fs33 ity of the church as a \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 church":\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li1641\sl253\slmult0\up0\fs24\par

\pard\li1641\sb37\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0\fs22 I. Local congregations ma\super\fs33 de up of Christians\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li1608\sb21\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0 2. Special meetings on the \super\fs33 first day of the week\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li1608\sb30\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0 3. Church officers (e\super\fs33 lders) who have responsibility for the\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

