\pard\fi724\li15\ri1321\sb108\sl259\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs22 I could fill hundreds of additional pages with various \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 other views as well as biblical exposition of the nature of the uni-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 versal and local church, but that is nor the primary purpose of \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 this volume. My concern is that readers recognize the validity \cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw1\f0 and essentiality of the local church \i\fs24 as a visible, contemporaneous \cf0\expndtw0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw2\i\f0\fs24 demonstration of the universal church and the primary impor-\cf0\expndtw0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0\fs24 tance that unity and community be demonstrated in its interper-\cf0\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw-3\i\f0\fs24 sonal relations.\cf0\expndtw0\i0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi705\li10\ri1365\sb34\sl264\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 One theological concept closely aligned here is the priest-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\dn4\f0 hood of believers. Actually only five passages in two books of the New Testament refer directly to the priesthood of believers; they are few enough to be reproduced here.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li9753\sl225\slmult0\up0\fs24\par

\pard\fi9\li672\ri1385\sb44\sl225\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs20 You also, like living stones, are being built into a spiritual house to be a holy priesthood, offering spiritual sacrifices acceptable to God through Jesus Christ. (1 Peter 2:5)\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li9753\sl227\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\fi4\li663\ri1379\sb3\sl227\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs20 But you are a chosen people, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people belonging to God, that you may declare the praises of him who called you out of darkness into his wonderful light. (1 Peter 2:9)\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li9753\sl230\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\fi9\li644\ri1389\sb2\sl230\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs20 To him who loves us and has freed us from our sins by his \dn4 blood, and has made us to be a kingdom and priests to serve his God and Father\f2\emdash\f0 to him be glory and power for ever and ever! Amen. (Revelation 1:5b-6)\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi9\li629\ri1375\sb229\sl233\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0\fs20 You are worthy to take the scroll and to open its seals, because you were slain, and with your blood you purchased men for God from every tribe and language and people and nation. You have made them to be \fs22 a \fs20 kingdom and priests to serve our God, and they will reign on the earth. (Revelation 5:9-10)\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi9\li615\ri1384\sb224\sl238\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs20 Blessed and holy are those who have part in the first resurrec-\cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs20 tion. The second death has no power over them, but they will be priests of God and of Christ and will reign with him for \fs22 a thousand \fs20 years. (Revelation 20:6)\cf0\f1\fs22\par

