\pard\li2918\sb176\sl253\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-8\f0\fs22 THE IMPLEMENTATION OF UNITY AND COMMUNITY\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi700\li2241\ri1266\sb146\sl260\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs18 It \fs22 is tempting to spend the rest of the chapter continuing \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the discussion of the biblical nature of the "communited" \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 church. But this book deals with team leadership. Up to this \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 point, I have tried to draw some biblical implications regarding \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the relationships we must maintain if we expect leadership teams \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 to work together effectively in the body of believers, whether that \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 be in the local church or in other Christian organizations. Now I \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 will deal briefly with four concepts that help form a pattern of \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ministry based, if not on specific verses of 1 Corinthians 12, at \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 least upon the general New Testament concept of the church as a\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2289\sb5\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0 unified body.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2289\sl253\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\li2289\sb157\sl253\slmult0\cf1\b\i\f0\fs22 A \b0 People-Centered Ministry\cf0\i0\f1\par

\pard\fi705\li2299\ri1237\sb136\sl265\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 In one sense we could say that the church should be the \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 most person-centered organization in the world. But the church \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 must be God-centered before it can be person-centered. Finding \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the proper balance between these two very important ingredients \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 of biblical life has proven too great a responsibility for some \super\fs33 con-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 gregations. They have slipped from the path e ither to the left (an \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 overemphasis on human relati\super\fs33 onships to the neglect of God's sov-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\dn4\f0 ereignty) or to the right \super\fs33 (a greater concern for "souls". than for \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 people).\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi715\li2313\ri1219\sl267\slmult0\qj\cf1\i\up0\f0 Christian love always finds \super\fs33 its outworking within the con-\cf0\nosupersub\i0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0 text of relationships. \super\i0\fs33 Yet precisely at this point many Christian \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\dn4\f0 leaders go sour. Ou\super\fs33 r problems testify not so much to our inability \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 to perform public ly as to our inability to get along wi\super\fs33 th people in \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 private, interper\super\fs33 sonal relations. The church is and always has\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li5323\sb143\sl230\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-7\b\up0\f0\fs20 16\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li11745\sl278\slmult0\fs24\page\par
\par

\pard\li1862\ri2652\sb134\sl278\slmult0\qj\tx2415\cf1\expndtw-8\b\f0\fs20 UNITY AND COMMUNITY \cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs20\tab\expndtw-8\b IN THE BODY\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li9883\sl260\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\li10\ri769\sb77\sl260\slmult0\qj\cf1\expndtw1\f0\fs22 been people, and service in it at any given time requires necessary relationship with those people. Adequate team leadership requires \expndtw2\dn4 awareness of and sensitivity to human need all around us, as well \expndtw0 as an appreciation of how we can meet that need through the \expndtw3 supernatural dynamics of God's truth and Spirit.\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi662\li10\ri775\sb2\sl258\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0 Consider, for example, a pastor who finds his self-satis-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 faction and fulfillment amid the books in his study, where he \dn4 spends all his time. Although his theology may be orthodox and his sermons scholarly, a dimension of reality could be missing from his ministry. His lifeline to meaningful ministry demands constant contact with people, so that he can learn to relate God's \expndtw1 truth to real problems in real lives.\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi662\li14\ri779\sb2\sl257\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Our Lord's ministry always centered on people; He \expndtw2 focused on meeting their spiritual and eternal needs. But this pri-\cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ority did not keep Him from showing interest in temporal and \expndtw2 physical needs as well. If our various "body parts" properly func-\cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\f0 tion together, it will be because we have discovered and imple-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\f0 mented a new-covenant view of interpersonal relations.\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\li9912\sl253\slmult0\up0\fs24\par

\pard\li33\sb128\sl253\slmult0\cf1\i\f0\fs22 The Gift of Leading\cf0\i0\f1\par

\pard\fi657\li29\ri750\sb142\sl257\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 In conjunction with the \fs20 spiritual gift of administration \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\i\f0 (kubernesis), \i0\fs20 a gift \fs22 of leadership appears as well \fs20 in Romans 12:8 \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 where Paul uses the word \i prohistemi.6 \i0 It literally means "to put \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 before" or "to go before." Originally it had the connotation of \cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\f0 presiding, conducting, directing, or governing. I have often asked \cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\f0 myself whether \i kubernesis \i0 and \i prohistemi \i0\fs20 represent \fs22 two differ-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ent gifts or two dimensions of the same gift, namely, congrega-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 tional leadership. As closely as these ideas are linked, we proba-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 bly must recognize them as two different gifts, both essential to \cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw-2\f0 effective ministry.\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi657\li52\ri736\sb7\sl257\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 In spite of today's popular emphasis on prestige and pub-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 licity, \i the New Testament concept \i0 of \i leadership emphasizes ser-\cf0\i0\f1\line\cf1\i\f0 vice. \i0 Those who utilize the gift of leadership (or administration) \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 must exemplify service and unity as models for the body. Some-\cf0\f1\par

\pard\sl240\slmult1\fs12\par
\par
\par

\pard\li3331\sl302\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\fi235\li3331\ri3259\sb210\sl302\slmult0\cf1\expndtw-7\b\f0\fs20 TEAM LEADERSHIP \cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\expndtw-7\b\f0\fs20 IN CHRISTIAN MINISTRY\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li1219\sl244\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\li1219\ri1266\sb146\sl244\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs22 how we must balance delegated authority and loving concern in our constant quest for biblical leadership.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi744\li1243\ri1247\sb68\sl215\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 D. Swan Haworth identifies three interesting concepts of staff relationships:\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2035\sl268\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\li2035\ri1247\sb55\sl268\slmult0\qj\tx2284\cf1\f0\fs22 1. A loosely organized staff which may have several "solo-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab ists" but no director, no regular rehearsals, and conse-\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2284\ri1233\sb9\sl259\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 quently very little harmony; people on such a staff relate to each other only by necessity;\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2040\sb19\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0 2. An integrated staff held together by one commander; or\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2049\sb16\sl253\slmult0\cf1\f0 3. A colleague relationship in which "each staff member\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li2303\ri1238\sl273\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 trusts the others, despite their difference. This colleague relationship requires each member of the team to be a responsible person."7\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi763\li1300\ri1219\sb271\sl279\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Relationships of the professional staff stand as a model \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 for any Christian ministry. Confusion and bickering at the top \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\fs26 will \fs22 not only destroy the working effectiveness of the manage-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\dn4\f0 ment team, but will filter down the ranks to distort inter\super\fs33 personal \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 relationships between other workers all the \super\fs33 way up and down the \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 line.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\li1296\sl276\slmult1\up0\fs24\par

\pard\li1305\sb144\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 The Requirement of a Bib\super\fs36 lical Lifestyle\cf0\nosupersub\i0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi758\li1296\ri1165\sb118\sl283\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 The Christian leader'\super\fs33 s behavior toward other people is \nosupersub\fs22 determined by inn\super\fs33 er qualities. To put it another way, interperson-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 al relations on a \super\fs33 horizontal plane arise from interpersonal rela \nosupersub\fs22 tions with God \super\fs33 on a vertical plane. We face so many people prob-\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0 lems in the chu\super\fs33 rch because we have somehow confused ourselves \nosupersub\fs22 into thinking t\super\fs33 hat what we \i\fs36 do \i0\fs33 for God is more important than \nosupersub\fs22 what we \i\fs24 are \super\i0\fs33 before God. A distinctly Christian lifestyle, with \nosupersub\fs22 shared min istries in a c\super\fs33 ommunal setting, requires the grace of \nosupersub\fs22 n mutual acc\super\fs33 eptance, a willingness to enter into mutual burde \nosupersub\fs22 bearing, an\super\fs33 d a generous \fs39 dose of active \fs33 love.\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li11164\sl273\slmult0\fs24\page\par
\par

\pard\li1977\ri3223\sb158\sl273\slmult0\qj\tx2545\cf1\expndtw-8\b\f0\fs20 UNITY AND COMMUNITY \cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs20\tab\expndtw-8\b IN THE BODY\cf0\expndtw0\b0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li9278\sl257\slmult0\fs24\par

\pard\fi19\li72\ri1364\sb132\sl257\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs22 knowing them as persons rather than merely as "employees." Paul Tournier points out two great fears that keep people from understanding each other: fear of being judged and fear of being \expndtw3 advised.8 Harsh criticism and flippant answers to troubling prob-\cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\f0 lems are two clubs that can bludgeon human relations to death. For example, some adults have no ministry with teenagers because they greet every attempt at communication with a handy \expndtw1 "Oh yes, I used to feel like that. You'll get over it."\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi672\li67\ri1379\sb26\sl246\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 The immorality of manipulation is not confined to Madi-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\dn4\f0 son Avenue. It is just as wrong for Christian leaders as for the \cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw3\f0 advertising executive who designs television commercials geared \cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\f0 to trick people into buying what they do not need and cannot \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 afford.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi676\li62\ri1379\sb57\sl257\slmult0\qj\cf1\expndtw2\up0\f0 In our pressure-cooker society, we find it difficult to grasp \expndtw0 and practice the biblical concept of patience. We tend to be obsessive and compulsive about our behavior, and frequently "come on too strong" in relationships with other people. I like the way Robert Lofton Hudson put it: "Impatience is a heresy of \expndtw3 the soul and an apostasy of the disposition."9\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

\pard\fi686\li48\ri1384\sb8\sl262\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0 Schaeffer called unity in love "the mark of the Christian" \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 and referred to that unity as "the final apologetic." He pointed \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 out that the world cares nothing for doctrine but has been given \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 the authority to judge the effectiveness and authenticity of the \cf0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\f0 church on the evidence of a loving lifestyle among members in its \cf0\expndtw0\f1\line\cf1\expndtw2\f0 community.\cf0\expndtw0\f1\par

