\pard\fi9\li2059\ri1281\sb121\sl238\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs22 us that no one person can be held responsible for communica-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\dn4\f0 tion; it is always a mutual process. The word \i\fs20 mutuality \i0\fs22 becomes \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 very important in recognizing the interrelated nature of commu-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 nication.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi729\li2049\ri1290\sb58\sl258\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0 Another term frequently used in sociological literature is \i\dn4\fs20 simultaneity. \i0\fs22 Communication is not like a Ping-Pong game in which messages are batted back and forth. Rather, the ongoing relationship between communicating people forms a simulta-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 neous process. People who effectively relate to other people rec-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 ognize that both what they say and what they hear pass through an emotional and cultural grid.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi763\li2006\ri1295\sb8\sl267\slmult0\qj\cf1\up0\f0 When a Sunday school superintendent speaks to a teacher, the meaning of her words is not so much inherent in what she says, as in the way the reacher interprets them. These two people \dn4 are simultaneously active in the communication process and therefore mutually responsible for what happens in their dia-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 logue. Each loads up little trucks (words) with cargo (ideas) and sends them on their way. At the same time, each one is unloading the trucks sent by the other person.\cf0\f1\par

\pard\fi830\li1896\ri1304\sl275\slmult0\qj\tx1987\tx1977\tx1972\tx1963\tx1953\cf1\up0\f0 Sociology assumes that human beings develop their hu-\cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0\tab man abilities through social interaction. The community (chu\super\fs33 rch, \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\tab school, or other institution) provides the context for an anal\super\fs33 ysis \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\tab of relationships. We might also add that \super\fs33 it provides the context \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\tab for believers to function as the b\super\fs33 ody of Christ, in keeping with \cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\tab the kind of patterns delineated \super\fs33 in \nosupersub\fs22 1 Corinthians 12 and similar \cf0\f1\line\cf1\f0 passages in the New Tes\super\fs33 tament. We are certainly not passive \nosupersub\fs22 recipients of everything \super\fs33 sociology and psychology tell us about \nosupersub\fs22 human relationships . But we must be astute discerners of tru\super\fs33 th \nosupersub\fs22 and willing to in tegrate information that fits our \super\fs33 understanding \nosupersub\fs22 of the special re\super\fs33 velation of God's Word.\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

