\pard\fi230\li24\ri4\sl181\slmult0\qj\cf1\expndtw1\f0\fs14\page Perhaps you have heard the saying. "If you fail to plan, you are \cf0\expndtw0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 planning to fail." Like most proverbs, it contains a truth. When we study Scripture, we sec that God Himself is our perfect model of planning. \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 From the beginning He declared His plan of redemption for man. We can also see divine planning in the lives of biblical characters as God directed their lives and influenced following generations. Joseph referred to the \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 plan God made many years before when he said to his brothers, "God sent me ahead of you to preserve for you a remnant on earth and to save your lives by a great deliverance" (Genesis 45:7).\cf0\f1\fs22\par

