\pard\li3912\sb37\sl161\slmult0\cf1\f0\fs14 Who Does Planning?\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi201\li3887\ri576\sb93\sl203\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs14 Who is responsible for the planning of the church? Each one is \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 different. In some churches, planning may be done by those who are \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 designated in the church constitution or charter. Or, in some small \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 churches, planning is done on the basis of informal agreements. In many \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 cases the church board might be considered a planning committee. If it is \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 a large church, each department may have a committee that is charged \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 with planning. However, if there are committees within departments, they \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 must have some way of relating to the church as a whole. What we arc \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 talking about here concerns planning for the whole church rather than one \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 aspect of it. There are some simple principles for you to follow if the \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 planning group is either your responsibility or that of someone you \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 designate.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi196\li3897\ri585\sb89\sl205\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs14 Planning functions arc usually done by a group or a committee. \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 Sometimes basic planning may be done by an individual, but somewhere in the process a committee or group must either be consulted or give \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 approval. There are certain principles about planning groups that \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 contribute to their success:\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi230\li3878\ri575\sb91\sl207\slmult0\qj\cf1\b\f0\fs14 1. \b0\i The group must be small enough to be functional. \i0 If the planning \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 group is too big, it is hard to assemble all of the members. The number of \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 members depends on what has to be accomplished. While three is usually \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 considered the minimum, five or seven members make a good working \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 group. However, if the committee is appointed for one special function \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 that includes many activities, you will need a larger group. Fur instance, a \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 M15510115 convention committee may include from eleven to fifteen \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 members, and subcommittees will be responsible for different activities. \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\b\f0\fs14 Each committee \b0 should be small enough to get the work done and large \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 enough to handle the tasks efficie ntly. You will find that most large\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi9\li10\ri2142\sl159\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs14\page segments of your church ministries must be represented. Som\super\fs21 etimes the \nosupersub\fs14 church ministries arc divided according to age groups, or t\super\fs21 hey may be \nosupersub\fs14 divided according to the purpose of the planning.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li10\ri2152\sb96\sl182\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs14 2 Circle the words describing factors that contribute to \b a \b0 successful \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs14 planning group.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

