\pard\fi196\li4046\ri762\sl172\slmult0\qj\cf1\f0\fs14 Most churches use a com\super\fs21 bination of the three organization types, with \nosupersub\b\fs14 very \b0 little of the direct line type. Chu\super\fs21 rch work includes a variety of tasks \nosupersub\fs14 so leaders and worke\super\fs21 rs relate to each other in functional ways. Functions \nosupersub\fs14 arc usually car\super\fs21 ried out in a pattern similar to this:\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4272\sb125\sl161\slmult0\tx4555\cf1\expndtw-7\f0\fs14 1. \expndtw0\tab Identify a goal \super\fs21 and the tasks needed to accomplish it\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4252\sb36\sl161\slmult0\tx4555\cf1\f0\fs14 2. \tab Allocate the tasks to \super\fs21 members of the group.\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4257\sb41\sl161\slmult0\tx4564\cf1\f0\fs14 3. \tab Determine relatio\super\fs21 nships of people and tasks to each other to avoid\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4555\sb16\sl161\slmult0\cf1\f0\fs14 overlapping.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4252\sb46\sl161\slmult0\tx4564\cf1\f0\fs14 4. \tab Keep organization \super\fs21 dynamic. Reorganize function and structure to\cf0\nosupersub\f1\fs22\par

\pard\li4569\sb40\sl161\slmult0\cf1\f0\fs14 meet needs.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

