\pard\li3441\sb34\sl138\slmult0\cf1\f0\fs12 LEADING\cf0\f1\fs22\par

\pard\fi201\li3403\ri784\sb88\sl179\slmult0\qj\tx3925\tx4808\tx5355\tx5754\tx6301\tx7501\cf1\f0\fs12 We have defined leadership as any contribution that comes from any \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 member of the group to achieve group goals. I like this definition because \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 it shows that leadership is not confined to one or a few people. In this \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 section of \i our \i0 lesson we will look at two main qualities that contribute to \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 good \tab leadership. \tab These \tab arc \tab "clear \tab communication" \tab and \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 "decision-making." First we will consider how to overcome barriers to \cf0\f1\fs22\line\cf1\f0\fs12 communication.\cf0\f1\fs22\par

